18/10/2002
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The For Macedonia Together coalition and the ethnic Albanian Democratic Union for Integration (DUI) expect to hammer out a final agreement on forming the new government Friday (18 October), according to Skopje media reports. Representatives of the parties confirmed that their teams completed negotiations late Thursday on the composition of the new government, to be headed by Social Democratic Alliance (SDSM) leader Branko Crvenkovski. They say only a few final details remain. According to sources from both SDSM and DUI, the ethnic Albanian partner expects to get one deputy prime minister seat, as well as the ministries of transport and communications, justice, healthcare and education. (MIA, Utrinski Vesnik, Vest - 18/10/02; A1 TV - 17/10/02)
